@17:20 that form factor is a perfect match for cases like the Krux Naos/Intertech IM1/Nox Xtreme (it comes with different brandings) or the SSUPD Meshroom D — i.e. cases that are designed to just barely fit a micro-ATX board (in case of the SSUPD you even need an extension base to actually with the full height).

I have the IM1 here with an mATX board and a full-size ATX PSU, and it's really tight for intake fans at the bottom (they interfere with the FP connectors at the edge of the mainboard) — YTX would really be _perfect_ in this case.

Only problem is that SFF cases generally don't have room for connectors on the back of the board (that would be kinda counter-productive to being small...). So to be actually useful they'd need to use a more traditional connector placement on the front.
